node.text:
what to do with it. I would get it, and then in less than a week, it was just . . . GONE! Those days were challenging, embarrassing and frustrating.
 
This is why I wanted to spend a whole episode talking about 10 things to NOT do when we get our paycheck. (Believe me, I’ve done some STUPID stuff with my paycheck, and I wish someone had told me this sooner.) Go check out the full episode to learn how to avoid those money mistakes so you can start stacking some serious cash.
 
Click the link in my bio.

node.text:
Congrats Queen! This is F R E E D O M ! Next stop… MILLIONAIRE STATUS. 

#Repost @lynn__henry
・・・
Here’s to breaking generational curses and building generational wealth!!!!

One year ago today, I accomplished one of my major goals and paid off all of my student loans in just 18 months. 93k paid in full!!!! 

I worked two jobs while living in Cali, one which was 20 minutes from where I lived and the other which was 1 hour away, but with traffic it would sometimes be 2 😭. I worked 4-6 days a week and lived off my budget like crazy!! Paid my first loan June 2019, my second March 2020 and my 3rd May 2020. 

Discipline, faith, prayer, and manifestation got me here!!! Thank you to all my family and friends who encouraged me along the way!!

I paid you off in 18 months and quadrupled my account in 11 months!!!! 

To God be the glory, I was DEBT FREE @28... I love it here!!!!!!!! . . .📸 @focalmuse
